life lately: in doodles 🎨 

idk why i’ve had such a hard time posting here for the last few months. i think i’m trapped in this cycle of perfection, the longer i hold out on posting, the more precious these silly little boxes seem. nothing feels good enough or worthy enough which is truly unhinged because we’re talking about tiny squares on an app on a cell phone. 

have i abandoned this idea of perfection? clearly not. because instead of posting these photos as is, i must still find a way to be ~different~ to be *special* because somehow the intention of imperfection, is far easier to swallow than failing the earnest endeavor.

so alas, here we are. decorating life to make it feel a little bit more special 🪩🍀

i wish i could do this to my brain 🫧

the end of a decade, but the start of an age 🎂
wishing for taylor to play new romantics tonight 🤞🏼
what if you just called taylor up and asked her to perform on your birthday?

i will never be the same 🪩 

i’ve been a taylor swift fan since debut. she voiced my soundtrack for middle school, high school, college, dropping out of college, and beyond. each album memorialized in an era of my life - the songs transporting me right back to where i was, and who i was back then. i knew i was excited for this tour, even more so when one landed on my birthday - but i didn’t understand HOW much this show would effect me. how it didn’t just feel like music. or nostalgia. it felt like growing up. it felt like a birds-eye view home movie of my entire adolescence. 

@taylorswift knows how to put on a show. but there’s something spectacular about putting on a show for not only the people in your audience, but their childhood and teenage selves too. pure magic ☁️🦋

and to the loml, thank you for getting us these tickets, dressing up with me, and making sure i had the best birthday possible 🤍 you are the best thing that’s ever been mine 🤍
